Lidar objects expose write(...) and deep_copy(...) with optional options. Use these options to tune archive size, cloud-read behavior, and downstream compatibility. library(whiteboxworkflows) l <- wbw_read_lidar('survey.las') # LAZ controls
l$write( 'survey_out.laz', overwrite = TRUE, options = list( laz = list( chunk_size = 25000, compression_level = 7 ) )
) # COPC controls
l$write( 'survey_out.copc.laz', overwrite = TRUE, options = list( copc = list( max_points_per_node = 75000, max_depth = 8, node_point_ordering = 'hilbert' ) )
)

